            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add 10g <span class=\"text-purple\">[15g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[20g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> to a microwave-safe jug with your <strong>sriracha </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> half </strong>your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>buffalo sauce mix</strong></p><p>Put the <strong>buffalo sauce mix </strong>in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 1 min or until the butter has melted, then mix until fully combined</p><p>Add 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>buffalo sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
